import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='lon', y='lat', hue='state', palette='tab20', legend=False)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude and latitude across all state capitals?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    state_counts = data['state'].value_counts().reset_index()
    state_counts.columns = ['state', 'count']
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    chart = sns.barplot(x='state', y='count', data=state_counts)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('Which state has the highest number of state capitals?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Number of State Capitals')
    
    max_state = state_counts.loc[state_counts['count'].idxmax()]
    plt.axhline(max_state['count'], color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Max: {max_state['state']} ({max_state['count']:.2f})")
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    first_letter_counts = data['first_letter'].value_counts().reset_index()
    first_letter_counts.columns = ['first_letter', 'count']
    chart = sns.barplot(x='first_letter', y='count', data=first_letter_counts, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of first letters of state capital city names?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('First Letter')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.legend(title='First Letters', loc='upper right', labels=first_letter_counts['first_letter'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    average_vowel_count = data['vowel_count'].mean()
    ax = sns.histplot(data=data, x='vowel_count', bins=5, kde=True)
    plt.axvline(average_vowel_count, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average: {average_vowel_count:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average number of vowels in state capital city names?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='lon', y='lat', hue='state', palette='tab20', legend=False)
    sns.regplot(data=data, x='lon', y='lat', scatter=False, color='black', line_kws={'linewidth': 1})
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between longitude and latitude of state capitals?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
